6 SECTION 1. Arkansas Constitution, Article 19, § 31(b), concerning the
7 independent citizens commission existing for the purpose of setting salaries
8 of elected constitutional officers of the executive department, members of
9 the General Assembly, justices, judges, and prosecuting attorneys, is amended
10 to add an additional subdivision to read as follows:
11 (9) By a vote of at least two-thirds (2/3) of the membership of
12 the Senate, the Senate may remove a member of the independent citizens
13 commission before the expiration of his or her term for cause only, after
14 notice and hearing.
15
16 SECTION 2. Arkansas Constitution, Amendment 33, § 4, is amended to
17 read as follows:
18 § 4. Removal of member — Procedure — Appeal.
19 The Governor shall have the power to remove any member of such boards
20 or commissions before the expiration of his term for cause only, after notice
21 and hearing. Such removal shall become effective only when approved in
22 writing by a majority of the total number of the board or commission, but
23 without the right to vote by the member removed or by his successor, which
24 action shall be filed with the Secretary of State together with a complete
25 record of the proceedings at the hearing.
26 An appeal may be taken to the Pulaski Circuit Court by the Governor or
27 the member ordered removed, and the same shall be tried de novo on the
28 record. An appeal may be taken from the circuit court to the Arkansas Supreme
29 Court, which shall likewise be tried de novo.
30 By a vote of at least two-thirds (2/3) of the membership of the Senate,
31 the Senate may remove a member of a board or commission under this amendment
32 before the expiration of his or her term for cause only, after notice and
33 hearing.
34
