23 SECTION 6. Arkansas Constitution, Article 5, is amended to add an
24 additional section to read as follows:
25 § 43. Removal of members of boards and commissions.
26 (a) By a vote of at least two-thirds (2/3) of the membership of the
27 Senate, the Senate may remove a member of a board or commission established
28 under this Constitution or Arkansas law before the expiration of his or her
29 term for cause only, after notice and hearing.
30 (b) The method for removal of a member of a board or commission under
31 subsection (a) of this section shall be supplemental to other methods of
32 removal provided for by this Constitution or Arkansas law.
